WEBVTT

00:02.215 --> 00:05.316
Barney, afraid this
is good-bye.

00:05.323 --> 00:07.190
Your buzz kill of a ma

00:07.192 --> 00:09.386
thinks I'm a... a bad
influence on you.

00:09.411 --> 00:10.611
What? That's...

00:10.891 --> 00:12.457
What is that word you taught me?

00:12.459 --> 00:14.726
"Bull" something?

00:14.728 --> 00:16.545
But she's your
mother and I'm...

00:16.547 --> 00:18.930
you know, I'm just
your Uncle Jerry.

00:18.932 --> 00:21.350
So, this is the last
time I can see you.

00:21.352 --> 00:23.835
But you're supposed to
take me to see

00:23.837 --> 00:25.837
that Zeppelin cover band
next week.

00:25.839 --> 00:28.340
The night is gonna be...

00:28.342 --> 00:30.776
Led-and-Jerry.

00:30.778 --> 00:32.610
Sorry, buddy,
but this is it.

00:32.613 --> 00:35.013
But don't you forget
your training.

00:35.015 --> 00:36.732
What's a magician's best friend?

00:36.734 --> 00:37.816
A drunk audience.

00:37.818 --> 00:39.184
Attaboy.

00:39.186 --> 00:42.738
You still got that button
from the festival we went to?

00:46.893 --> 00:50.195
Now... I'm gonna put this

00:50.197 --> 00:52.197
right inside your brain,
behind your ear...

00:54.000 --> 00:56.435
so that I'll know that
you won't forget me.

00:58.171 --> 00:59.337
See you, buddy.

01:00.539 --> 01:02.741
And hey...

01:02.743 --> 01:06.678
Never... stop... partying.

01:09.282 --> 01:12.484
<i>Kids, in 1983,</i>
<i>Barney watched his father</i>

01:12.486 --> 01:13.952
<i>walk out of his life.</i>

01:13.954 --> 01:17.689
<i>And in 2011, when their</i>
<i>first reunion ended badly...</i>

01:17.691 --> 01:20.358
I'd love nothing more
than to be a part of your life.

01:20.360 --> 01:22.227
<i>This time it was Barney</i>
<i>who did the walking.</i>

01:22.229 --> 01:23.528
Bye.

01:23.530 --> 01:26.164
<i>And that was almost</i>
<i>the end of it.</i>

01:26.166 --> 01:28.100
<i>Except, a few weeks later...</i>

01:28.102 --> 01:31.636
I am so angry at my dad!

01:31.638 --> 01:33.572
Guess who called me today.

01:33.574 --> 01:35.907
Go on, guess.
Mmm.

01:35.909 --> 01:38.243
Your dad?
My dad!

01:38.245 --> 01:40.445
Barney Stinson.

01:40.447 --> 01:41.747
Hi, Barney. It's your dad.

01:42.615 --> 01:43.682
Look, would you
like to go fishing

01:43.684 --> 01:45.283
with me and J.J.
on Sunday morning?

01:45.285 --> 01:48.186
Ooh, hold on, let me
check my personality.

01:48.188 --> 01:50.789
Oh, no. Turns out I would never
do that in a million years.

01:50.791 --> 01:52.724
Barney, look...

01:52.726 --> 01:55.060
I know you're disappointed
that your dad is just...

01:55.062 --> 01:57.929
a boring old driving instructor
from the suburbs.

01:57.931 --> 02:01.533
But that guy I used to be--
"Crazy Jerry"?

02:01.535 --> 02:03.468
He was bad news!

02:03.470 --> 02:05.904
Drinking, partying,
sleeping around.

02:05.906 --> 02:08.406
The party can't go on forever.

02:08.407 --> 02:11.409
You're 35; I'm-I'm sure
you're starting

02:11.411 --> 02:12.878
to realize that, right?

02:12.880 --> 02:16.615
You do not know
how right you are.

02:16.617 --> 02:17.949
Zero right!

02:17.951 --> 02:20.585
We're not getting too old for anything.
You sure?

02:20.587 --> 02:23.088
I feel like we collectively
learn the opposite lesson,

02:23.090 --> 02:24.589
like, at least once a year.

02:25.759 --> 02:27.793
I have to face an ugly truth.

02:27.795 --> 02:31.096
Jerry Whittaker, my own father,

02:31.098 --> 02:33.465
is anti-awesome-etic.

02:34.200 --> 02:35.367
I know

02:35.369 --> 02:37.235
Crazy Jerry's still
in there somewhere,

02:37.237 --> 02:40.572
but he's trapped under 20 years
of lawnmower parties

02:40.574 --> 02:42.741
and carpool barbecues.
Wow,

02:42.743 --> 02:44.810
you know nothing
about the suburbs.

02:44.812 --> 02:47.813
Well, this Saturday night,
I am bustin' him out.

02:47.815 --> 02:48.880
I'm gonna

02:48.882 --> 02:50.649
make Jerry realize he was wrong

02:50.651 --> 02:53.552
about giving up his old life
by showing him

02:53.554 --> 02:56.788
the awesomest night
of all time.

02:56.790 --> 02:58.423
And for the awesomest night

02:58.425 --> 03:02.928
of all time, I'm going to need
the awesomest friends

03:02.930 --> 03:04.162
of all time.

03:06.232 --> 03:07.833
Okay, who do I know?

03:11.404 --> 03:13.038
Guys...!

03:14.640 --> 03:16.641
Do any of you know
George Clooney?

03:17.727 --> 03:19.110
Okay, my dad's almost here.

03:19.112 --> 03:20.412
I need everything to be

03:20.414 --> 03:22.531
as awesome as possible tonight.

03:22.533 --> 03:24.049
That's why you
brought these guys.

03:24.051 --> 03:28.019
No. That's why
I brought <i>these</i> guys.

03:28.021 --> 03:29.020
I've made some

03:29.022 --> 03:30.622
minor improvements
to your identities.

03:30.624 --> 03:31.756
Uh.
Mm!

03:31.758 --> 03:32.924
You'll find them
on these cards.

03:32.926 --> 03:33.992
Improvements?!
Yeah.

03:33.994 --> 03:36.878
Bro, we are
already the four

03:36.880 --> 03:40.498
jiggity-jamminest dudes
and dudettes this side of...

03:40.500 --> 03:42.651
Okay, let's see the cards.

03:42.653 --> 03:44.102
Robin, no one watches the news

03:44.104 --> 03:46.338
unless it's a car chase
or a nip slip.

03:46.340 --> 03:47.205
You are now

03:47.207 --> 03:48.723
a professional scotch taster.

03:48.725 --> 03:49.875
Mm!

03:49.877 --> 03:51.743
Lily, Jerry needs to learn
that other lifestyles

03:51.745 --> 03:53.311
are just as fulfilling
as monogamy,

03:53.313 --> 03:55.714
so now you and Marshall
are in an open marriage.

03:55.716 --> 03:57.983
Whoo-hoo!
Gross!

03:57.985 --> 04:00.385
Also, Marshall,
you can't just be unemployed,

04:00.387 --> 04:01.553
so you are now

04:01.555 --> 04:04.189
a gin-swilling,
womanizing playwright.

04:05.024 --> 04:07.425
And, Ted, just be yourself.

04:08.461 --> 04:10.061
Just kidding.

04:10.063 --> 04:13.198
Here's a giant pile of topics
you should avoid talking about.

04:13.200 --> 04:15.433
Well. Well, this could
actually be fun.

04:15.435 --> 04:18.536
In fact, I believe it
was Oscar Wilde who said,

04:18.538 --> 04:21.172
"Man is least himself
when he talks..."

04:21.173 --> 04:22.340
Ted, card.
Ah.

04:22.342 --> 04:24.976
You're right--
"No quoting Oscar Wilde."

04:24.978 --> 04:26.478
Finally...

04:26.480 --> 04:28.146
Robin, you're dating Ted.

04:28.148 --> 04:29.547
Aw, man!

04:29.549 --> 04:30.949
Why?

04:30.951 --> 04:32.183
I can't have

04:32.185 --> 04:33.985
any single female friends
lying around.

04:33.987 --> 04:36.488
My dad'll be all,
"Why don't you marry Robin?

04:36.490 --> 04:37.989
"You guys are cute together.
Deep down, you know

04:37.991 --> 04:40.759
you were never happier
than when you were with her."

04:40.761 --> 04:41.860
Uh...

04:41.862 --> 04:43.228
no, thanks.

04:43.230 --> 04:45.030
Hey, Barney-- love
the new identities.

04:45.032 --> 04:48.266
Little thing-- instead of
being a naked super ninja,

04:48.268 --> 04:51.836
can I be Meryl Streep
in <i>The Devil Wears Prada?</i>

04:51.838 --> 04:54.105
How good was that movie?
Oh, my God.

04:56.076 --> 04:57.175
And...

04:57.177 --> 04:59.945
hence new identities.

05:01.213 --> 05:04.249
<i>And so Barney's dad</i>
<i>finally showed up.</i>

05:04.251 --> 05:06.551
Jerry, you remember Marshall--
he's a well-known writer.

05:06.553 --> 05:07.919
Playwright.
We're all writers,

05:07.921 --> 05:11.006
just some of us don't know
what our story is yet.

05:11.724 --> 05:13.791
Lily, his wife.

05:13.793 --> 05:15.961
Well, most nights.
Mama don't let no ring

05:15.963 --> 05:18.029
get in the way of a good time.

05:18.031 --> 05:19.931
That's... a
little depressing.

05:19.933 --> 05:21.066
Uh, hi again.

05:21.068 --> 05:22.167
Ted. Oh, and, Jerry,

05:22.169 --> 05:24.319
you remember my girlfriend.
Robin. Hi.

05:24.321 --> 05:26.471
So nice to see you again.

05:26.473 --> 05:28.273
Wait, wait. Jerry,

05:28.275 --> 05:29.674
I got to tell you
the truth.

05:29.676 --> 05:30.875
Guys, I'm gonna tell him.

05:31.677 --> 05:33.311
We're also a band.

05:33.313 --> 05:34.946
<i>Two, three, four!</i>

